            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper and onion have softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min or until the vegetables are tender and the stock has thickened to a stew-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
